  The two highest-priority items are both ALIGN proposals:

  1. Proposal 9 (critical): WriteAsync drops the Arc<DmaBuffer> after SPDK
  submission but before NVMe DMA completes — use-after-free that can cause data
  corruption. Fix: pin the buffer in PendingOp until the completion callback
  fires.
  2. Proposal 2 (moderate): ControllerReset only cancels the requesting client's
   pending ops, not all clients'. Other clients get undefined behavior
  post-reset. Fix: iterate all clients and cancel their pending ops before
  issuing the hardware reset.

  Let me know which proposals you'd like to act on, or if you want to
  review/modify any of them.

