     Plan: Fix Proposal 2 (FR-009 reset scope) and Proposal 9 (WriteAsync buffer
      lifetime)

     Context

     Two bugs in src/actor.rs:

     1. WriteAsync buffer lifetime (critical): Command::WriteAsync extracts a
     raw pointer from Arc<DmaBuffer> for SPDK DMA, but doesn't retain the Arc —
     the buffer can be freed while NVMe hardware is still reading from it.
     ReadAsync has the same bug with Arc<Mutex<DmaBuffer>>.
     2. ControllerReset scope (moderate): ControllerReset handler only cancels
     pending ops for the requesting client. A hardware reset invalidates ALL
     in-flight NVMe commands across all queue pairs, leaving other clients'
     operations in undefined state.

     File: src/actor.rs

     Change 1: Add buffer fields to PendingOp (line 108)

     Add two optional buffer fields to pin DMA memory for the duration of async
     operations:

     pub(crate) struct PendingOp {
         pub handle: u64,
         pub deadline: Instant,
         pub qpair_idx: usize,
         pub read_buf: Option<Arc<Mutex<DmaBuffer>>>,
         pub write_buf: Option<Arc<DmaBuffer>>,
     }

     Need to add use std::sync::Mutex; to the imports. DmaBuffer is already
     accessible via interfaces::DmaBuffer (re-exported from spdk_types).

     Change 2: Pin buffer in ReadAsync handler (line 408-415)

     Store buf.clone() in the PendingOp:

     PendingOp {
         handle,
         deadline: ...,
         qpair_idx: qp_idx,
         read_buf: Some(buf.clone()),
         write_buf: None,
     }

     Change 3: Pin buffer in WriteAsync handler (line 484-491)

     Store buf.clone() in the PendingOp:

     PendingOp {
         handle,
         deadline: ...,
         qpair_idx: qp_idx,
         read_buf: None,
         write_buf: Some(buf.clone()),
     }

     Change 4: Update all other PendingOp constructions

     Three sites total:
     - Line 410 (ReadAsync) — gets read_buf: Some(...) (Change 2)
     - Line 486 (WriteAsync) — gets write_buf: Some(...) (Change 3)
     - Line 937 (test) — add read_buf: None, write_buf: None

     Change 5: Move ControllerReset out of dispatch_command (lines 627-651)

     The current dispatch_command is a static method that only has access to one
      client's pending_ops. To cancel ALL clients' ops on reset, we need to:

     1. Don't handle ControllerReset inside dispatch_command — instead, return
     early with a signal (or handle it before calling dispatch_command).
     2. Add a new method on BlockDeviceHandler (instance method, has &mut self):

     fn handle_controller_reset(&mut self, requesting_client_id: u64) {
         // Cancel ALL clients' pending ops
         for client in &mut self.clients {
             for (&h, _) in client.pending_ops.iter() {
                 let _ = client.session.callback_tx.send(Completion::Error {
                     handle: Some(OpHandle(h)),
                     error: NvmeBlockError::Aborted("cancelled due to controller
      reset".into()),
                 });
             }
             client.pending_ops.clear();
         }

         // Perform the actual hardware reset
         let rc = unsafe {
     spdk_sys::spdk_nvme_ctrlr_reset(self.controller.as_ptr()) };
         let result = if rc == 0 {
             self.controller.refresh_namespaces();
             Ok(())
         } else {
             Err(NvmeBlockError::BlockDevice(
                 interfaces::BlockDeviceError::ProbeFailure(format!(
                     "spdk_nvme_ctrlr_reset failed with rc={rc}"
                 )),
             ))
         };

         // Send ResetDone only to the requesting client
         if let Some(client) = self.clients.iter().find(|c| c.session.id ==
     requesting_client_id) {
             let _ = client.session.callback_tx.send(Completion::ResetDone {
     result });
         }
     }

     3. In poll_clients, detect Command::ControllerReset before dispatching:

     In the Ok(cmd) arm of the poll loop (line 232), check if cmd is
     ControllerReset. If so, call self.handle_controller_reset(client_id) and
     continue instead of calling dispatch_command.

     Ok(cmd) => {
         if matches!(cmd, Command::ControllerReset) {
             let client_id = self.clients[i].session.id;
             self.handle_controller_reset(client_id);
             continue;  // continue inner loop polling this client
         }
         // ... existing dispatch_command call
     }

     4. In dispatch_command, replace the ControllerReset arm with unreachable!()
      or remove it entirely (since it's now handled in poll_clients).

